EULOGY 01 | The wake is spent. The estate will now account for it, name by name.
EULOGY 02 | BLUE gave 2 pennies to the ground and the tolls. Generosity is only ever involuntary here.
VERIFY_SNAP res://verify_out/stirs_c/snap_eulogy_13102.png
EULOGY 03 | RED hoarded 30 pennies and spent it on nothing. The manor respects the discipline; the will does not reward it.
EULOGY 04 | We commend GOLD, who bought 18 wreaths with other people's grief and now owns a house that owns them back.
EULOGY 05 | And MINT — who took from no one all night, and wept at two graves besides — was in the estate's estimation, almost kind.  How unusual.
EULOGY 06 | The estate adds, for the record: GOLD has been paid in blood money before. The ledger rounds up.
EULOGY 07 | The reading rests. Your debts are noted, your kindnesses doubted, and the door is, as ever, that way.
